03/04/85 chcpass

Syntax as a command:  chcpass Person_id


Function:  changes the user's card input password in the PNT found in
>sc1.  Thus, even if the user has changed his password with the -cpw
control argument on the ++PASSWORD card, the chcpass command overrides
the user's change.

A card input password may consist of from one through eight ASCII
printing characters, including backspace, but excluding space and
semicolon.


Arguments:
Person_id
   is the Person_id of the user whose card input password is to be
   changed.
